messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Fire emergency. My mom is in the bathroom and she can't get up.
Okay, are there other people at home with you?
I have a little sister, a big sister, two big brothers, and my dad, but my dad and big brothers aren't home.
Is your dad at home with you?
No, he's at work.
Okay, so you're home alone with your mom and your little sister?
Yeah.
Is your mom awake?
Yeah, she threw up and then she fell and can't get up.
Is she still talking to you?
Yeah.
Can you take the phone to her?
Yeah. Mom, he wants to talk to you. No, she can't talk right now.
Okay, what exactly happened? Did she pass out?
Yes.
How old are you?
I'm 4.
Alright, help is on the way. Do you know the address?
We live on Bounty Drive.
Okay, I have that. The firemen are on the way. Stay on the phone with me, okay? I'll tell you when you need to open the door for them.
Okay.
Has your mom been sick the last couple of days?
Um, yeah, she sometimes gets sick a lot.
Okay. Is your little sister there with you?
Yeah, she's in her high chair.
How old is she?
I don't know, she can't crawl but she can walk and talk.
Okay, so she's probably around 2 years old?
Yeah.
What is she having for dinner?
Noodles.
Okay, and your mom made those for her?
Yes, but I'm not having noodles because I'm waiting for my toy house.
Alright. What does your dad do for work?
He works near the Jelly Bean factory.
Okay, we can ask your mom for more details when the firefighters get there.
Okay.
Do you have any pets?
Yes, two dogs. One is in my brother's room and the other is in my room.
Can you close the door to the rooms they're in so the firemen don't scare them?
Yeah, I can do that.
Great job. Just stay on the phone with me. How's your mom doing?
She's still awake but starting to get sleepy.
Okay, the firefighters are almost there. Are you near the front door?
No, but I can go there.
That's fine. Just unlock it and stay inside until they arrive.
Okay.
Are you still with me?
Yes.
They're almost there. Do you still see your mom?
Yes, she's in the bathroom.
Okay, you've done a great job. The emergency responders will be there any second now.
Okay.
